<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation author="Faulwetter, Sarah" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="281 - 326" title="An account of the taxonomy and distribution of Syllidae (Annelida, Polychaetes) in the eastern Mediterranean, with notes on the genus Prosphaerosyllis San Martin, 1984 in the Mediterranean" volume="150" year="2011">Faulwetter et al. (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
based on a single specimen. In the Mediterranean also known from Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Somaschini, Alessandra" journalOrPublisher="Atti della Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali Memorie" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="83 - 94" title="Policheti della biocenosi ad alghe fotofile (facies a Corallinaelongata) nel lazio settentrionale" volume="95" year="1988">Somaschini 1988</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Nygren, Arne" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 314" title="Revision of Autolytinae (Syllidae: Polychaeta)" volume="680" year="2004">Nygren (2004)</bibRefCitation>
restricts its distribution to the North-East Atlantic and North-East Pacific. Mediterranean specimens could be misidentifications in which the trepan was overlooked. In addition, the Greek specimen was identified using the key and description by 
<bibRefCitation author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="MartÃ­n">Martin</normalizedToken>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
which, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Nygren, Arne" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 314" title="Revision of Autolytinae (Syllidae: Polychaeta)" volume="680" year="2004">Nygren (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, corresponds only in part to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Myrianida" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Myrianida inermis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inermis">Myrianida inermis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
